  "faqs": [
    {
      "question": "Is Agenta really open source?",
      "answer": "Yes. The core platform is open source under a permissive license and you can self-host the full stack for free, forever. The cloud plans add managed hosting, higher limits, and team features on top."
    },
    {
      "question": "What counts as a trace?",
      "answer": "A trace is one end-to-end run of your LLM app or agent — every step, prompt, tool call, and response captured for observability. Plans are metered on traces per month, with pay-as-you-go for overages."
    },
    {
      "question": "Can I switch plans or cancel anytime?",
      "answer": "Yes. Upgrade, downgrade, or cancel from your workspace settings at any time. Annual plans are billed yearly at a 20% discount; monthly plans renew month to month."
    },
    {
      "question": "Do you offer discounts for startups or academia?",
      "answer": "We do. Early-stage startups, students, and researchers can apply for discounted or free access — reach out to the team and tell us about your project."
    },
    {
      "question": "What happens when I hit my usage limit?",
      "answer": "Nothing breaks. You can enable pay-as-you-go for extra traces and seats, or upgrade to the next plan. We notify you before you reach your limit so there are no surprises."
    },
    {
      "question": "How does Enterprise self-hosting work?",
      "answer": "Enterprise customers can deploy Agenta in their own cloud or on-prem with SSO/MFA, SOC 2, audit logs, and a dedicated SLA. Our team supports the rollout and ongoing operations."
